def replacer(theatres_df: pd.DataFrame):
    cat = list(theatres_df.columns[theatres_df.dtypes == 'object'])
    for column in theatres_df.columns:
        if column in cat:
            mode = theatres_df[column].mode()[0]
            theatres_df[column] = theatres_df[column].fillna(mode)
        else:
            mean = theatres_df[column].mean()
            theatres_df[column] = theatres_df[column].fillna(mean)
    print('Missing values replaced')
replacer(theatres_df)

Missing values replaced

Univariate - Single Column Visualization¶

categorical - countplot
continuous - histogram
In [88]:
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns

def plot_count(df: pd.DataFrame, col: str):
    plt.figure(figsize=(12,12))
    sns.countplot(data=df, x=col)
    plt.title(f'Countplot for {col}')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90, fontsize=8)
    plt.show()

def plot_histogram(df: pd.DataFrame, col: str):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10,3))
    sns.histplot(data=df, x=col, kde=True)
    plt.title(f'Histogram for {col}')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90, fontsize=8)
    plt.show()

for con in continuous:
    plot_histogram(theatres_df, con)

for cat in categorical:
    plot_count(theatres_df, cat)

In [126]:
# Bivariate functions
def plot_scatter(df: pd.DataFrame, x: str, y: str):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10,3))
    sns.regplot(data=df,x=x,y=y)
    plt.title(f"Scatterplot for {x} and {y}")
    plt.xticks(rotation=90, fontsize=8)
    plt.show()

def plot_reg(df: pd.DataFrame, x: str, y: str):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10,3))
    sns.regplot(data=df, x=x, y=y, line_kws={"color":"Red"})
    plt.title(f"Regplot for {x} and {y}")
    plt.xticks(rotation=90, fontsize=8)
    plt.show()

def plot_box(df: pd.DataFrame, x: str, y: str):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10,3))
    sns.boxplot(data=df, x=x, y=y)
    plt.title(f"Boxplot for {x} and {y}")
    plt.xticks(rotation=90, fontsize=8)
    plt.show()

def crosstab_heatmap(df: pd.DataFrame, cat_col1: str, cat_col2: str):
    ctab = pd.crosstab(df[cat_col1], df[cat_col2])
    # print(ctab)
    plt.figure(figsize=(12,12))
    sns.heatmap(ctab, annot=True, fmt="d")
    plt.title(f"Crosstab Heatmap for {cat_col1} vs {cat_col2}")
    plt.show()

Show Top 3 Capacity theatres by City¶

In [136]:
# Show Top 3 Capacity theatres by City
top_3_capacity_theatres_by_city = (
    theatres_df.groupby(by = "City")
    .agg({"Avg Capacity":"sum"})
    .nlargest(3, "Avg Capacity")
    .round(2)   
)
